        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p>for “Alinatia.”</p>
            <p>via <placeName>New York</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Curacao</placeName>
                <date>14th June 1869</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Mr. Isc. Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>Philada.</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">I have to acknowledge<lb/> the receipt of your kind form of
                    <date>26. Apl.</date> with the Occidents accom<lb/>panying. I have noted all you
                remark about you Books l<add>?</add>. nevertheless<lb/> I cannot get the people here
                to buy them in consequence of their size and<lb/> weight, if you could print them in
                smaller <sic>additions</sic> and in the<lb/> thinner paper I have 4 setts engaged
                besides many that I think would<lb/> sell even at a Reasonable <add>?</add>ha charge
                I <del>sale</del> showed my letter from you<lb/> to <persName>Mr Nathan</persName>
                and he has promised to write you he has <add>?</add> some of<lb/> your small Books
                as you will see as fr. <add>?</add> sales I enclose you,<lb/> and by
                        <del><add>?</add></del> which you will see there is $90.42<lb/>100 due you
                less 68¢ for 2<lb/> years subscriptions of <persName>Doctr.
                    DeYong<add>?</add></persName> who lately died and his wife has<lb/> not the
                means of paying, hence I do not consider it altogether<lb/> lost she may some day
                pay.</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">I have requestd. my friends <persName>Mrss Joseph
                    T<add>?</add></persName><lb/> then to hand you on my a<lb/>c 90.42<lb/>100 franc
                pieces <add>or the equivalent</add> at 1$ each is $90.42 fr which<lb/> you are
                    <sic>debitted</sic>, please mention formally<add>?</add> of our Sunday School as
                it is<lb/> coming in very well as almost all the first families here have taken</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>interest in it and many of the first respectable and talented young<lb/> ladies have
                taken part as teachers &amp;c <persName>Mr Ca<add>?</add></persName> was to have
                from<lb/> me an Account of the Advancement of the School level he has not<lb/> come
                so in time to come by this level when he gives it me<lb/> I will forward it</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">I am Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Your very Ob S &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <persName role="author">M Daunt</persName>
            </p>
            <pb n="2V"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(center)indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
